<Project>
  <!--
    Ocr.Vellum 0.2.3+ handles the native-svg2pdf/pdf2svgwrapper path mismatch
    entirely at runtime via a DllImportResolver in Vellum.Interop.Pdf2SvgNativeResolver.
    The resolver loads pdf2svgwrapper.dll by absolute path from
    runtimes/<rid>/native/, which forces Windows to resolve the 40+ sibling
    deps (glib, gobject, gio, cairo, poppler, ...) from that same folder via
    LOAD_WITH_ALTERED_SEARCH_PATH.

    Earlier versions shipped a build-time copy that mirrored the bundled
    natives into a sibling native-svg2pdf/ folder. That created two copies of
    every DLL in the output directory, which made assembly-scanning tools
    (e.g. Wolverine's extension discovery) touch native DLLs and correlated
    with GLib double-init crashes. Removed.
  -->
</Project>
